    "Part 4": "DDLPS originate from adipocyte stromal progenitor cells",
    "step 1": {
        "implementation details": "Integrate all tumor cells from DDLPS-WD samples into a single dataset using Harmony with parameters theta=2, lambda=0.1. Identify clusters based on gene expression profiles using Seurat's FindClusters function with resolution=0.6. Assign the identified clusters to previously identified signatures: adipocytic differentiation, stemness, ECM remodeling, hypoxia, invasion, and angiogenesis.",
        "original text": "To better characterize the stemness population of tumor cells and determine if these cells could be DDLPS progenitors, all tumor cells from DDLPS-WD samples were selected and re-integrated together in a single dataset. Tumor cells showed consistent MDM2 and CDK4 expression and specific expression of the previously identified signatures: adipocytic differentiation (clusters 1, 2, 3, 4, 7, and 8), stemness (clusters 5, 6, 9), ECM remodeling and hypoxia (cluster 0), invasion (clusters 1, 8 and 11), and, in a very low proportion, angiogenesis (cluster 10).",
        "results": "Tumor cells from DDLPS-WD samples showed consistent MDM2 and CDK4 expression and were classified into clusters based on gene expression profiles. These clusters were assigned to specific gene expression signatures: adipocytic differentiation (clusters 1, 2, 3, 4, 7, and 8), stemness (clusters 5, 6, 9), ECM remodeling and hypoxia (cluster 0), invasion (clusters 1, 8, and 11), and angiogenesis (cluster 10).",
        "results original text": "Tumor cells showed consistent MDM2 and CDK4 expression and specific expression of the previously identified signatures: adipocytic differentiation (clusters 1, 2, 3, 4, 7, and 8), stemness (clusters 5, 6, 9), ECM remodeling and hypoxia (cluster 0), invasion (clusters 1, 8 and 11), and, in a very low proportion, angiogenesis (cluster 10)."
    },
    "step 2": {
        "implementation details": "Compare the stemness signature of tumor cells with previously reported signatures of mammalian adipocyte stromal progenitor cells (ASPC) found in normal white adipose tissue. Identify similarities in gene expression profiles between DDLPS stemness cells and early multipotent adipocytic progenitors described in previous studies (G1, Merrick et al.; hASPC2, Emont et al.; P1, Schwalie et al.).",
        "original text": "We next compared this stemness signature with previously reported signatures of mammalian adipocyte stromal progenitor cells (ASPC) found in normal white adipose tissue and characterized by scRNA-seq and found that the stemness cells in DDLPS were highly similar to early multipotent adipocytic progenitors described in previous studies (G1, Merrick et al.; hASPC2, Emont et al.; P1, Schwalie et al.).",
        "results": "The stemness cells in DDLPS were highly similar to early multipotent adipocytic progenitors described in previous studies, including G1 (Merrick et al.), hASPC2 (Emont et al.), and P1 (Schwalie et al.).",
        "results original text": "We next compared this stemness signature with previously reported signatures of mammalian adipocyte stromal progenitor cells (ASPC) found in normal white adipose tissue and characterized by scRNA-seq and found that the stemness cells in DDLPS were highly similar to early multipotent adipocytic progenitors described in previous studies (G1, Merrick et al.; hASPC2, Emont et al.; P1, Schwalie et al.)."
    },
    "step 3": {
        "implementation details": "Conduct scRNA-seq on tumor cells using the 10X Genomics platform with a read length of 100 bp and a depth of 50,000 reads per cell. Identify the expression of canonical markers such as CD55, CD34, CD44, ALDH1A3, MFAP5, PI16, and DPP4 using Seurat's FindMarkers function with parameters min.pct=0.25 and logfc.threshold=0.25. Validate the presence of these markers in different tumor cell clusters.",
        "original text": "In particular, these cells were characterized by overexpression of adipocyte stem cells canonical markers including CD55, CD34, CD44, ALDH1A3, MFAP5, PI16 and DPP4, whereas other tumor cell clusters expressed markers of preadipocytes or adipocytes in line with their adipocytic differentiation.",
        "results": "The stemness cells in DDLPS were characterized by overexpression of canonical markers such as CD55, CD34, CD44, ALDH1A3, MFAP5, PI16, and DPP4, while other tumor cell clusters expressed markers of preadipocytes or adipocytes.",
        "results original text": "In particular, these cells were characterized by overexpression of adipocyte stem cells canonical markers including CD55, CD34, CD44, ALDH1A3, MFAP5, PI16 and DPP4, whereas other tumor cell clusters expressed markers of preadipocytes or adipocytes in line with their adipocytic differentiation."
    },
    "step 4": {
        "implementation details": "Perform immunohistochemical staining using MDM2 (SantaCruz, ref NCL-L-CD163, clone 10D6, pH6, dil 1:100) and CD55 (CST, ref 31759, clone E7G2U, dil 1:600, pH 9) antibodies to identify the presence of MDM2+CD55+ cells within the WD component of DDLPS tumors. Incubate the sections with primary antibodies for 1 hour at room temperature, followed by washing with PBS. Validate the presence and distribution of these cells in the fibrous septa interspersed between tumor adipocytes.",
        "original text": "Immunohistochemical staining using MDM2 and CD55 antibodies showed the presence of MDM2+CD55+ cells within the WD component of DDLPS tumors. These cells were present in the fibrous septa interspersed between tumor adipocytes and showed marked atypia.",
        "results": "MDM2+CD55+ cells were identified within the WD component of DDLPS tumors. These cells were present in the fibrous septa interspersed between tumor adipocytes and showed marked atypia.",
        "results original text": "Immunohistochemical staining using MDM2 and CD55 antibodies showed the presence of MDM2+CD55+ cells within the WD component of DDLPS tumors. These cells were present in the fibrous septa interspersed between tumor adipocytes and showed marked atypia."
    },
    "step 5": {
        "implementation details": "Perform in situ multiplex immunofluorescence in a cohort of 7 WD components of DDLPS using the Opal\u21227-Color IHC Kits (Akoya Biosciences, ref NEL821001KT). Use the following antibodies: CD55 (dil 1:800), CD44 (dil 1:3000), ALDH1 (dil 1:1000), CD34 (dil 1:200), and MDM2 (RTU). Confirm the presence of cells coexpressing MDM2 with multiple ASPC markers including CD55, CD44, CD34, and ALDH1.",
        "original text": "In situ multiplex immunofluorescence in a cohort of 7 WD components of DDLPS confirmed the presence of cells coexpressing MDM2 together with multiple ASPC markers including CD55, CD44, CD34 and ALDH1.",
